-- 2012-09-03T11:41:41Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-03/india-defeats-new-zealand-by-5-wickets-in-second-cricket-test.html
Virat Kohliâ€™s unbeaten 51 helped
push  India  to victory over  New Zealand  by 5 wickets in their
second cricket Test in Bangalore as the home team secured a 2-0
victory in the two-match contest.  India finished its second innings 262-5 to win. Kohli
combined with MS Dhoni for 96 to lead the hosts. Dhoni was not
out on 48 when the match ended.  New Zealand added 16 runs to its overnight second-innings
score of 232-9 on day four before  Zaheer Khan  had Jeetan Patel
given out caught behind for 22. India spinner Ravi Ashwin
finished with 5-69, his third five-wicket haul of the series.  India won the first Test at Hyderabad by an innings and 115
runs.  The teams also are scheduled to play two Twenty20
internationals on Sept. 8 and 11.  To contact the reporter on this story:
